mission: The Racine Art Museum (RAM) is an outgrowth of the Charles A. Wustum Museum of Fine Arts (Wustum) which opened in 1941. Duplications of effort, and the real possibility of a few taking advantage of the charity of others, were also of great concern. The agency began with a tiny budget, a few volunteers, and a very part-time staff person. Since 1987, the agency has grown in budget, staff, and number of volunteers.
